                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The wight's unarmed attacks and bound weapons inflict a curse that makes a creature grow weak and spiteful. If a wight inflicts corrupting spite on a creature already afflicted by it, the victim attempts a new save, ignoring the result if it's better than a failure.</p>\n<p>A living humanoid that dies while under the curse rises as a wight after [[/br 1d4 #Wight Spawn Timer]]{1d4 rounds}, controlled by the wight that killed it. The wight spawn can't inflict corrupting spite and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2}. If its creator dies or after roughly a month of existence, the new wight becomes autonomous and turns into a normal wight</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[type:fortitude|dc:17];</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 1} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 2} and doesn't treat any creatures as allies (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> As stage 2, except @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 3} (1 round)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> As stage 2, except @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 4} (1 round).</p>"
